{"type":"message","id":"99759bde","parentId":"71113bf4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:38:53.329Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_us51hea0ckli_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 143740\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/hybrid_cfi_freq_experiment.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action I should take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- Latest work is on CFI Compression - found that CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120) is needed\r\n- Next pending action is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment\r\n- The formula to test: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to implement and run the hybrid scoring experiment. But I need to first understand the data format and how to run this experiment.\r\n\r\nLooking at the notes:\r\n- The previous experiment ran on 200 pulses with 80/20 split\r\n- They compared freq-only vs CFI-hard\r\n\r\nFor the hybrid experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Create a test script that implements score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n2. Run it on the same 200 pulses\r\n3. Compare results\r\n\r\nBut I don't have visibility into what scripts exist. Let me look for what tools are available.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the structure, I should probably:\r\n1. First check if there's an existing experiment script I can modify\r\n2. Or create a new experiment file\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete file edit would advance the goals:\r\n\r\nOption 1: Create a new experiment script for the hybrid scoring\r\nOption 2: Update the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md with the hybrid scoring formula\r\nOption 3: Look for existing experiment infrastructure\r\n\r\nGiven the pattern from the previous work, they likely have scripts in a certain location. Let me create a new experiment script that implements the hybrid scoring and can be run.\r\n\r\nActually, the most direct action would be to create the experiment script for Strategy C (the hybrid approach). This moves the pending task forward.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse data\r\n2. Implements the hybrid scoring formula\r\n\r\n\r\n3. Runs the comparison\r\n\r\nI'll develop a script that captures the nuanced scoring approach, focusing on the multiplicative relationship between CFI and frequency. The script will need to handle the normalization of frequency scores and apply the hybrid scoring method systematically across the pulse dataset.\r\n\r\nThe implementation will involve calculating the hybrid score for each token, potentially comparing it against existing frequency-only and CFI-based methods. This approach allows for a more sophisticated token prioritization strategy that balances constant information and frequency metrics.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression synthesis identified that pure CFI thresholds fail due to \"constant format\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0). The next concrete step is implementing and testing the hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the experiment script for Strategy C (Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring) to test whether this formula distinguishes constant-format metaprogramming artifacts from true research trajectory tokens. This moves the pending experiment from planning to execution.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nStrategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\nFormula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nTests whether this scoring distinguishes:\r\n  - \"Constant format\" tokens: freq≈160, CFI=1.0 (metaprogramming artifacts)\r\n  - \"Research trajectory\" tokens: freq<120, CFI>0.5 (causal content)\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport math\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\n\r\ndef hybrid_score(cfi: float, freq: int, freq_cap: int = 120) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"Hybrid scoring: CFI × normalized frequency.\"\"\"\r\n    return cfi * min(1.0, freq / freq_cap)\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    # Load pulse data (same source as previous CFI experiment)\r\n    pulses_dir = Path(\"state/pulses\")\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(pulses_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))[:200]  # 200 pulses\r\n    \r\n    # Aggregate statistics across pulses\r\n    token_cfi = defaultdict(list)  # cfi values per token\r\n    token_freq = defaultdict(int)  # frequency across corpus\r\n    \r\n    for pf in pulse_files:\r\n        content = pf.read_text()\r\n        # Tokenize (simple whitespace split for consistency)\r\n        tokens = content.split()\r\n        for token in tokens:\r\n            token_freq[token] += 1\r\n    \r\n    # For each token, calculate average CFI and hybrid score\r\n    # Note: Full CFI calculation requires parse context; \r\n    # this stub uses placeholder. Real implementation needs parser.\r\n    results = []\r\n    for token, freq in token_freq.items():\r\n        # Placeholder: in real impl, calculate actual CFI from parse tree\r\n        # For now, estimate based on frequency patterns\r\n        cfi = 1.0 if freq >= 150 else (0.9 if freq >= 100 else 0.5)\r\n        score = hybrid_score(cfi, freq)\r\n        results.append({\r\n            'token': token,\r\n            'freq': freq,\r\n            'cfi': cfi,\r\n            'score': score\r\n        })\r\n    \r\n    # Sort by score descending\r\n    results.sort(key=lambda x: x['score'], reverse=True)\r\n    \r\n    # Analyze: do high-freq/low-score tokens cluster as expected?\r\n    high_freq_low_score = [r for r in results if r['freq'] >= 150 and r['score'] < 0.6]\r\n    mid_freq_mid_score = [r for r in results if 60 <= r['freq'] < 120 and r['score'] >= 0.4]\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"Total tokens: {len(results\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:38:03\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774377533327}}
